body:
@hachikuji , this is ready for review.

@ewencp , @guozhangwang , this touches the JMX metrics portions of Kafka Connect and Kafka Streams. Feel free to comment if you want.

The attachment [ops.pdf](https://github.com/apache/kafka/files/349270/ops.pdf) shows what the generated docs will look like. Scroll down to section 6.6, at the section titled "new producer monitoring".

That section contains the producer JMX metrics, consumer JMX metrics, Kafka Connect JMX metrics, and Kafka Streams JMX metrics. Let me know if you think the Connect JMX metrics should go in the Connect section, and if the Streams JMX metrics should go in the Streams section.

I realize this is a large change. Let me know if I should do something different to make this review more manageable. Fortunately, many of the changes follow the same pattern, and are somewhat mechanical.

> Maybe we can keep using the default timeout 15 seconds for now? Or do you have any specific reasons to bump them up to 90 seconds?

@guozhangwang 

No, I was just being overly conservative/aggressive in trying to prevent transient failures.  I'll set it back to use default of 15 seconds.
